    "body": "## Summary\n\nThis fixes dtype-changing alias views on packed sub-byte dtypes such as `float4_e2m1fn -> uint8`.\n\nThe main issue was that layout inference still reasoned in bytes, which breaks as soon as two logical elements share the same byte. On top of that, reshape would flatten packed sub-elements and lose the pack-lane information entirely.\n\nThis patch:\n- switches alias layout propagation from bytes to storage bits\n- teaches `Layout::Reshape` and `Fragment::Reshape` to preserve a trailing pack lane for packed subtype views\n- adds coverage for `T.view` on `float4_e2m1fn -> uint8`, including a shared-memory compile/run case\n\n## Validation\n\n- `python debug/0319_issue/reproduce.py`\n- `python -m pytest testing/python/language/test_tilelang_language_view.py -q`\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **Bug Fixes**\n  * Improved reshape behavior for sub-byte element types, preserving packed-storage semantics when changing element bitwidths (automatic pack-lane handling).\n  * More robust dtype-reinterpretation views (e.g., fp4↔uint8) with consistent physical storage preservation.\n\n* **Documentation**\n  * Clarified that reshape rescaling uses bit-level (per-element) storage footprint and notes pack-lane implications.\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Added tests validating sub-byte view reinterpretation and a CUDA-path compile/run for fp4→uint8 views.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
